---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  path="/work/persevere"
  title="Persevere Now — Platform Team Leadership | Steven Balalis"
  description="Case study: led 14-person platform team, product roadmap, A/B onboarding tests, and platform scale-up at a B2B SaaS company."
>
  <header class="case-study-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Case study · Team leadership</p>
      <h1>B2B Platform Operations</h1>
      <p class="meta">Persevere Now · Program Manager · Nov 2022 – May 2025 · B2B SaaS · Remote</p>
      <div class="metric-row">
        <div class="metric-box"><strong>14</strong><span>direct reports</span></div>
        <div class="metric-box"><strong>A/B</strong><span>onboarding experiments</span></div>
        <div class="metric-box"><strong>CEO</strong><span>facing metrics cadence</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <article class="case-study-body">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Context</h2>
      <p>
        Persevere Now runs a B2B platform serving instructional and operational workflows. The product
        team needed clearer roadmap ownership, faster onboarding improvements, and playbooks for
        integrations and configuration.
      </p>

      <h2>Problem</h2>
      <p>
        Onboarding drop-off was hurting activation. The backlog spanned multiple years without a
        consistent PO cadence. Platform ops, data analysts, and instructional staff needed one delivery
        rhythm and CEO-visible metrics.
      </p>

      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>
        Led product roadmap and Scrum backlog while managing 14 direct reports across platform ops,
        data analysts, and instructional staff — people leadership plus hands-on delivery ownership.
      </p>

      <h2>Approach</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Ran multi-year Jira backlog and sprint delivery as product owner</li>
        <li>Designed and ran A/B tests on onboarding flows; iterated from usage data</li>
        <li>Reported platform metrics to the CEO on a regular cadence</li>
        <li>Wrote SOPs for onboarding, integrations, and configuration</li>
        <li>Increased platform capacity through process and staffing coordination</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Outcome</h2>
      <p>
        Onboarding drop-off reduced through data-informed A/B iterations. Delivery cadence stabilized
        with a groomed backlog and playbooks that outlasted individual projects. Leadership had
        consistent metrics instead of anecdotal updates.
      </p>

      <p><a href="/">← Back to portfolio</a></p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
